Package: dipca
Type: Package
Title: Dynamic Inner Principal Component Analysis
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person(given = c("Bradley", "R."),
    family = "Buchsbaum",
    role = c("aut", "cre"),
    email = "brad.buchsbaum@gmail.com")
Description: Implements Dynamic Inner Principal Component Analysis (DiPCA),
    Dynamic Inner Canonical Correlation Analysis (DiCCA), and Dynamic Inner
    Partial Least Squares (DiPLS) for multivariate time series analysis.
    These methods extract latent components that follow autoregressive models,
    enabling temporal prediction and reconstruction. Based on the methods of
    Dong and Qin (2018) <doi:10.1016/j.jprocont.2017.05.002> for DiPCA,
    Dong and Qin (2018) <doi:10.1016/j.ifacol.2018.09.379> for DiCCA, and
    Dong and Qin (2018) <doi:10.1016/j.jprocont.2018.04.006> for DiPLS.
    Integrates with the 'multivarious' package framework for consistent
    preprocessing and projection interfaces.
